On [[September 28]], [[2005]], Google announced a long-term research partnership with [[NASA]] which would involve Google building a 1-million square foot R&D center at NASA's [[Ames Research Center]]. NASA and Google are planning to work together on a variety of areas, including large-scale data management, massively distributed computing, bio-info-nano convergence, and encouragement of the entrepreneurial space industry.
